th Pass / treatment passport\n- 18-23/05/2026: Active communication\n- 21/05/2026: **HUGE - Mum received a leaflet from Acorn Medical Practice about Empagliflozin (a diabetes drug she takes!) - side effects warning** - this is recent and very relevant\n- 21/05/2026: Andie reassures her it's just an info leaflet\n- 23/05/2026: Recent activity\n- 25/05/2026: Recent activity\n- 03/06/2026: Missed call from Andie\n\n**Context for what \"GH Pass\" is:**\nLooking at the chat: \"01/05/2026, 19:47\" - sent YouTube links and a RAI video (Italian TV - \"La Vera Storia di No232 - Nadya Otoo\" from 2016 Zecchino d'Oro, an Italian song contest) and then `GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf`. The video is about a Ghanaian-Italian child's story on Italian TV. So GH = Ghana. This is likely either:\n- A Ghanaian passport/travel document\n- A Ghana Health Service medical passport\n- Or a \"GH Pass\" = Ghana Health Insurance (NHIS) card\n\nThe timing (May 2026, near when the original PIP disallowance was in October 2021) and the context of recent emigration/immigration discussions suggests this might be related to her returning to Ghana or accessing Ghanaian health services.\n\n**Health Crossroads document (Dec 2025):**\n- 15 pages, sent to her saying \"for you to watch and understand maa\"\n- Then sent visuals: \"your health\", \"your situation\"\n- Said \"you need to change your diet\"\n- Then on 07/12/2025: \"All these will make you better pls read carefully and check the VISUALS\"\n- This sounds like a major health intervention document - probably Andie's creation (with AI help) explaining her diagnoses, the implications, what she needs to do to improve. The \"crossroads\" name suggests a critical decision point in her health.\n\n**Plain Language Record (Deborah_Plain_Language_Record.docx):**\n- Binary file, can't read directly\n- Likely a related document - probably the underlying source of the Health Crossroads PDF or a simpler version\n\n**So my picture is:**\n\n1. **Most recent active work (April-May 2026)**: PIP review submission (PIP.1043 form)\n   - The AI had helped him break down the 12 activities\n   - The \"Completing PIP Review Submission.md\" / \"Great_Completing PIP Review Submission.md\" / \"PIP&Laura.md\" are all the AI conversation logs\n   - The deadline was 12 March 2026 - so it should have been submitted by then\n   - Actually looking at the chat on 11/03/2026 \"Call me when free\" - this might be around submission\n   - On 12/03/2026 there's a missed call\n   - On 23/04/2026: \"Please just call em when you done reading\" - this suggests there's still a document to read/call to make\n   - \"If you contact us, use this reference.pdf\" - this is a DWP reference letter (in the PIP folder)\n   - 30/01/2026 letter and 8/04/2026 letter (letters DWP sent)\n\n2. **Health intervention (Dec 2025)**: Created and sent Health Crossroads document to mum with dietary change advice\n3. **Ghana travel/health (May 2026)**: Sent GH Pass document and links to Ghanaian-Italian content\n4. **Medication review (May 2026)**: Acorn Medical Practice sent her a warning about Empagliflozin side effects (her diabetes med)\n5. **Active carer role**: Booked her taxi, called doctors, transferred money, etc.\n6. **Plain Language Record**: A doc Andie is creating/has created (binary, need to read)\n\n**Now the question is: what does the user want to know?**\n\nThe user asked: \"find me all that you can parsing through all files in downloads folder on deborah efua ennin's diabetes but also all that ive done for her so far and where at and what i should be looking at next.\"\n\nSo they want:\n1. Files about Deborah's diabetes (in Downloads) ✓\n2. All work done for her so far ✓\n3. Where we're at ✓\n4. What to look at next\n\nI should now write a comprehensive answer. Let me also do a couple more checks to make sure I have the full picture:\n- Read the Plain Language Record (need to convert docx to text)\n- Read the Health Crossroads PDF (key document)\n- Read the GH Pass PDF (most recent)\n- Check the latest DWP letters\n\nLet me try to read the docx by using a different method. Also, I should check the workspace/scratchpad for any notes we (Mavis + Andie) have made.\n\nActually, the user said \"carry on\" so they want me to continue. Let me do a focused read of the remaining critical docs, then write a comprehensive summary. The most important things to read are:\n- GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf (most recent, May 2026) - what is this?\n- Deborah_s_Health_Crossroads.pdf (Dec 2025) - the health intervention\n- The most recent DWP letter (April 2026)\n- The Plain Language Record (if I can convert it)\n\nLet me try to read the docx and the PDFs. PDFs can be read by the read tool but docx is binary.\n\nLet me also check if there's a docx to text converter or use Python.",
