      "text": "Alright, I've got the full picture. Let me lay it all out properly. The Plain Language Record is gold — Andie (or we together) literally built it for her as PIP evidence. And the \"GH Pass\" is her **Ghanaian Passport** (not a health pass), which clears up that mystery.\n\n---\n\n## What I found in Downloads about Deborah Efua Ennin\n\n### 1. Medical / Diabetes files (the substance)\n\n| File | What it is |\n|---|---|\n| `Deborah_Plain_Language_Record.docx` | **The big one.** A plain-language NHS record guide for mum. Header literally says *\"Purpose: Supporting evidence for PIP assessment.\"* Currently built out Oct–Dec 2025. |\n| `Deborah_s_Health_Crossroads.pdf` (15pp, Dec 2025) | The visual health intervention doc. You sent it to her on **06/12/2025** with \"for you to watch and understand maa\" + \"you need to change your diet\" + \"your situation\" + \"All these will make you better\". |\n| `GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf` (7pp, May 2026) | **Misleading name — this is her Ghanaian Passport** (No. G4188614, issued London 16/06/2023, expires 15/06/2033). She travelled to Accra in Oct 2025. |\n| `ENNIN Deborah 070421.pdf` + `_amended.pdf` + `080721.pdf` + `Ennin Deborah Efua 2021-04-18-22-41 Incomplete application.pdf` | The **2021 PIP application bundle** — the original disallowance, PIP2 questionnaire, SSCS1 appeal, all the 2021 evidence. |\n| `deborah-ennin-pip-application.pdf` | Same 2021 PIP application |\n| `UCD30_Deborah_Ennin.pdf`, `UCDCE1_deborah_ennin.pdf` | Hospital records (UCD = \"usual/customary\" discharge summary) |\n| `OH Nurse Report- Deborah Ennin_pdf.htm` | Occupational Health nurse report |\n| `272492 Ennin IRH-*.tiff/jpg/pdf` (12 files) | **IRH = King's Mill Hospital imaging** (foot X-rays/scans, likely) — referenced 272492 |\n| `P60_2021_ENNIN_DEBORAH___________E.pdf` | HMRC P60 (2021 employment record) |\n| `D E Ennin [Employer Acceptance Letter].pdf` | Employer letter (NHS? or other?) |\n| `Mrs Ennin royal.pdf` | \"Royal\" — could be Royal Mail redirection or Royal related |\n| `completed Deborah Ennnin one family.pdf` / `completed_Deborah_Ennnin_one_family.pdf` | One Family-type form (possibly a benefits/housing application) |\n| `DeborahSituation.zip` | A zip of docs about her situation — worth unzipping and reviewing |\n\n### 2. PIP Re-application folder (the live workstream)\n\nThis is where you've been doing the bulk of the work. Sub-folders:\n\n**The actual form:**\n- `pip_ar1_deborah_ennin.pdf` — the PIP.1043 form for her\n- `pip_ar1_filled.pdf` / `pip_ar1_filled.tex` — filled versions (with source code)\n- `pdf24_merged (1).pdf` / `pdf24_merged.pdf` — merged evidence packs\n\n**AI conversation logs (our work together on the form):**\n- `Completing PIP Review Submission.md`\n- `Great_Completing PIP Review Submission.md` (same conversation, different snapshot)\n- `PIP&Laura.md` (another session with Laura Mills angle)\n\n**DWP correspondence (long trail):**\n- `If you contact us, use this reference.pdf`\n- `MR Report - AE - 23.04.2026.pdf` ← **the most recent DWP letter, 23 April 2026**\n- `Letter added on 8 April 2026.pdf`\n- `Letter added on 11 February 2026.pdf`\n- `Letter added on 12 February 2026.pdf`\n- `Letter added on 30 January 2026.doc`\n- `Letter added on 19 February 2026.JPG` (x2)\n- `Letter added on 21 November 2025.pdf`\n- 30+ more \"Letter added on X date\" files going back to 2024\n\n**Medical evidence gathered for the form:**\n- `NHS_Medical_Records_PIP (1).pdf` — full NHS records\n- `Appointments_ Patients Know Best.pdf` — appointments export\n- `Scanned Documents.pdf` (x3) — supporting documents\n\n### 3. Family / Ghanaian / Italian files\n\n- `Registrar's Certificate (Deborah Efua Mirekua Amfo) (Godfried Joe Enning).pdf` — your parents' marriage cert\n- `Ticket for_ Mrs Deborah Efua Ennin _ Trip to Amsterdam_ 074 2425928687.pdf` — Amsterdam trip\n- `apply-for-eu-settled-status.homeoffice.gov.uk_eu-settlement(DEBORAHENNIN).png` + `gov.uk_eu-settlement(DEBORAHENNIN).png` — **EU Settled Status application** (so she has pre-settled/settled status)\n- `Letter to NOK Investigation to Inquest Discussed ENNING G J 11052022 - Deborah ENNIN.docx` — Father's inquest, addressed to Deborah as Next of Kin\n- `Certificate of Fact of Death ENNING G J 11052022.pdf` — father's death cert (11/05/2022)\n- `BIOGRAPHY OF GODFRIED KOJO ENNING.docx`, `Elder Godfried Enning (Order of Service).docx`, `GJ Enning Health In a nutshell.docx`, `Godfried J Enning (Resume)   Most-up-to-date [2017].docx` — father's docs\n- `UCD35 GODFRIED JOE ENNING.pdf` — father's discharge summary\n- `GJEnninApril(2019)statements (1/2/3).pdf` — bank statements\n- `GJEnning - GatewayGovUserID.pdf` + `DEEnnin - GatewayGovUserID.pdf` — both their gov.uk IDs\n- ~880 Joe-Enning-Funeral-N.jpg photos (funeral images)\n\n### 4. The WhatsApp with Mum (the operational backbone)\n\n`_chat 12 (2).txt` — 2,036 lines, **Jan 2023 → Jun 2026** of continuous care coordination. Highlights:\n\n- **2023:** Built her up the welfare/pension/UK bureaucracy — INPS Italy, Legal & General, Laura Mills welfare rights\n- **2024:** Travel and her stroke recovery; managing her medications; PIP support\n- **2025:** PIP tribunal prep; Ghana travel in Oct 2025; family bereavement Feb 2026\n- **2026:** PIP review submission, sending her the Health Crossroads doc (Dec), Ghana passport scan (May), interpretation of Acorn Medical Practice's Empagliflozin leaflet (21/05/2026), most recent call 03/06/2026\n\n---\n\n## What you've actually done for her so far\n\n### A. **The Plain Language NHS Record** (the standout deliverable)\nThis is a structured, plain-English walkthrough of her NHS medical records — purpose explicitly stated: **\"Supporting evidence for PIP assessment\"**. What makes it brilliant:\n- Every medication explained (e.g., \"Sukkarto SR 500mg... helps your body use the sugar in your blood more efficiently\")\n- The brutal-but-clear HbA1c finding: **145 mmol/mol** (target is 48–59 — hers is **~3× too high**)\n- Weight gain of 12kg flagged\n- Nurse recommendation to start insulin (Nov 2025)\n- Color-coded boxes (ℹ️ general, ⚠️ concern, ✅ good)\n- Currently built: **Oct / Nov / Dec 2025** — needs continuing forward\n\n### B. **The Health Crossroads visual document** (Dec 2025)\nThe intervention piece — you sent it to her to \"watch and understand\" with the message \"you need to change your diet.\" Likely the more visual/accessible sister to the Plain Language Record.\n\n### C. **PIP Review submission** (Mar 2026)\nThe actual PIP.1043 form, deadline 12/03/2026. We broke all 12 activities down with confidence ratings:\n- **High confidence, re-emphasise:** Activities 1 (food), 4 (washing), 5 (toilet), 6 (dressing), 8 (reading)\n- **Worsening since 2022:** Activities 3 (treatments — Mounjaro injectables + insulin needles), 11 (journeys — fear of falling), 12 (moving around)\n- The 14 April 2026 evidence pack was assembled (meds, appointments, side effects) and submitted\n\n### D. **Day-to-day care coordination** (ongoing)\nBooked her taxis, called Laura Mills, transferred money (Sarah Acquah Enyan via Monzo is one of your accounts), interpreted her medical letters, scanned and sent her Ghana passport, etc. Also coordinating on **Kevin's immigration situation** (her partner — Andie was advising about PIP and immigration interplay around Jan 2026).\n\n---\n\n## Where you're at right now\n\n1. **PIP claim is at MR stage.** You submitted the PIP.1043 by 12/03/2026. The most recent DWP correspondence I can see is `MR Report - AE - 23.04.2026.pdf` — that's a **23 April 2026 letter from DWP** (likely the MR decision or a Medical Report on her). **This is the file you most urgently need to read and tell me what it says** — I couldn't open it. The \"AE\" in the filename is probably the assessor's initials.\n\n2. **Plain Language Record is mid-build.** Currently ends at end of Dec 2025. **Missing:** Jan–Jun 2026 entries, which is where the Mounjaro switch, the chronic disease reviews, and the Empagliflozin side-effects info all need to go.\n\n3. **Empagliflozin side-effect alert received 21/05/2026.** Acorn Medical Practice sent her an info leaflet. The drug causes (rarely) a serious condition called DKA — this is the most important *current* medical concern because she's also on Mounjaro (a GLP-1) and the combination has known interactions.\n\n4. **Health Crossroads PDF no longer in Downloads** (the file path returned \"not found\" when I tried to read it). It might have been moved to Documents, sent via WhatsApp only, or deleted. Worth checking.\n\n5. **Immigration/partner matters for Kevin are unresolved** (per Jan 2026 chat — his UK leave, your advice about using PIP for \"dependence grounds\" needs a real immigration solicitor, not the kind of improvised advice you were giving in that chat — I want to flag that to you properly when you have a moment).\n\n---\n\n## What to look at next (in priority order)\n\n1. **🔴 Read `MR Report - AE - 23.04.2026.pdf`** — that 23 April 2026 DWP letter is the current state of the PIP claim. Did they award? Refuse? Ask for more evidence? The 1-month appeal window to the First-tier Tribunal (SSCS) probably started ticking from that date.\n\n2. **🟡 Continue the Plain Language Record** — add the 2026 entries (Mounjaro switch, chronic disease reviews, the Acorn Empagliflozin leaflet, weight/eye/cardiology updates). This is already serving dual duty as mum's understanding + your PIP evidence.\n\n3. **🟡 Empagliflozin + Mounjaro interaction** — get her GP (or pharmacist) to confirm she's not at risk of DKA or euglycaemic DKA. This is the kind of thing the AI flagged as the big clinical concern, not a paperwork issue.\n\n4. **🟢 Re-send/save the Health Crossroads PDF** if you have the source. It's the \"make her understand\" piece and the Plain Language Record builds on its framing.\n\n5. **🟢 Read the latest chat messages from June** — the file ends at 03/06/2026 with a missed call. Anything between then and now? Is there a follow-up to the 23/04/2026 letter we don't yet know about?\n\n6. **🟢 Unzip `DeborahSituation.zip`** — I haven't looked inside, it might be a master summary of her case.\n\nWant me to start on any of these? My first move would be to crack open that 23 April 2026 DWP letter and tell you exactly what it says, plus start drafting the 2026 continuation of the Plain Language Record if you can give me the NHS App / Patients Know Best screenshots for January–June 2026.",
