      "text": "EUREKA! Now I have the full picture. The Plain Language Record is REAL and it's a document Andie is creating for his mum. It says:\n\n**\"NHS Patient Medical Record - Plain Language Guide for Mrs Deborah Ennin\"**\n- Patient: Mrs Deborah Ennin\n- Practice: Churchside Medical Practice\n- Purpose: \"Supporting evidence for PIP assessment\"\n\nThis is a document Andie (with the AI's help) is creating to:\n1. Help his mum understand her medical records\n2. Serve as evidence for her PIP assessment\n\nIt includes:\n- December 2025 entries\n- November 2025 entries  \n- October 2025 entries\n- All medications explained in plain language\n- Critical findings like HbA1c 145 (extremely high, normal is 38-42, diabetic target is 48-59) - her diabetes is severely uncontrolled\n- Weight gain of 12kg\n- Recommendations to start insulin\n- Visits in November, December 2025, etc.\n\n**The GH Pass document** is actually her **Ghanaian Passport** - not a health document!\n- Republic of Ghana Passport\n- Number: G4188614\n- Name: ENNIN DEBORAH EFUA\n- Nationality: Ghanaian\n- DOB: 06 Oct 1968\n- Place of Birth: Accra\n- Date of Issue: 16 Jun 2023\n- Expiry: 15 Jun 2033 (10-year validity)\n- Issued in London\n- Has travel stamps to Ancona, Italy (19-07-23, 12-07-23) and from Accra, Ghana (18 Oct 2025) and Heathrow (18 Oct 2025)\n- So she DID travel to Ghana in October 2025\n\nWait, the file is named \"GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf\" - GHPass = Ghana Passport. That makes sense now.\n\nSo the \"GH Pass\" was a copy of her Ghanaian passport that he was sharing with her or sending to her. Or it was for an Italian visa application or something. Looking at the chat context from 01/05/2026:\n- He sent YouTube links including a RAI Italian TV video about a Ghanaian girl\n- Then sent the GH Pass document\n- This was a few days after she had sent him the death/funeral announcement (20/02/2026)\n\nSo possibly:\n- He sent her the passport scan for an Italian visa application\n- Or for renewal\n- Or for some Ghanaian documentation\n- The Italian travel (Ancona stamps from July 2023) suggest she's been to Italy\n\n**Health Crossroads** - file is missing! The chat log shows Andie sent it on 06/12/2025 with the message \"for you to watch and understand maa\" and then \"your health\" and \"your situation\" and \"you need to change your diet\". I bet this is essentially the parent/precursor document to the Plain Language Record - a more visual one explaining her health situation. It's gone now from the Downloads folder or moved.\n\nNow I have everything I need. Let me write a comprehensive, organized response for Andie.\n\nKey things to include:\n\n**1. FILES FOUND IN DOWNLOADS ABOUT DEBORAH'S DIABETES (organized by category):**\n\nA) **PIP Application folder** (the main active work):\n- `pip_ar1_deborah_ennin.pdf` - her PIP form\n- `pip_ar1_filled.pdf/.tex` - filled version\n- `Completing PIP Review Submission.md` - AI conversation about completing it\n- `Great_Completing PIP Review Submission.md` - another version of same\n- `PIP&Laura.md` - another AI conversation\n- `pdf24_merged.pdf` and variants - merged evidence files\n- `NHS_Medical_Records_PIP (1).pdf` - NHS records for PIP\n- `Scanned Documents.pdf/.doc` - multiple versions\n- Many \"Letter added on X date\" files - DWP correspondence from 2024-2026\n- `If you contact us, use this reference.pdf` - DWP reference letter\n- `MR Report - AE - 23.04.2026.pdf` - Most recent DWP letter (23 April 2026)\n\nB) **Medical Records** (outside PIP folder):\n- `Deborah_Plain_Language_Record.docx` - **The big one - it's a comprehensive plain-language version of her NHS records specifically created \"as supporting evidence for PIP assessment\"** - starts with Dec 2025, Nov 2025, Oct 2025 (still being built)\n- `Deborah_s_Health_Crossroads.pdf` (15 pages, 06/12/2025) - the visual health intervention document sent to mum saying \"for you to watch and understand maa\", \"you need to change your diet\"\n- `GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf` - actually her **Ghana Passport** (G4188614), issued 16 Jun 2023, expires 15 Jun 2033\n- `ENNIN Deborah 070421.pdf` and variants - **Original 2021 PIP application documents** (SSCS1, PIP2, etc.)\n- `UCD30_Deborah_Ennin.pdf`, `UCDCE1_deborah_ennin.pdf` - hospital/medical records\n- `OH Nurse Report- Deborah Ennin_pdf.htm` - occupational health nurse report\n- `Ennin Deborah Efua 2021-04-18-22-41 Incomplete application.pdf` - 2021 incomplete application\n- `deborah-ennin-pip-application.pdf` - 2021 PIP application\n- `Mrs Ennin royal.pdf` - Royal something (maybe Royal Mail?)\n- `Mrs Ennin royal.pdf`\n- `273492 Ennin IRH-32.tiff` - hospital imaging (IRH = likely King's Mill Hospital)\n\nC) **P60 and employer docs**:\n- `P60_2021_ENNIN_DEBORAH___________E.pdf` - tax document\n- `D E Ennin [Employer Acceptance Letter].pdf` - employer letter\n- `GJEnninApril(2019)statements (1/2/3).pdf` - bank statements\n\nD) **Ghanaian/Italian documents** (for immigration/travel):\n- `GHPassDeborah_merged (1).pdf` - Ghana Passport\n- `apply-for-eu-settled-status.homeoffice.gov.uk_eu-settlement(DEBORAHENNIN).png`\n- `gov.uk_eu-settlement(DEBORAHENNIN).png` - EU settled status\n- `Ticket for_ Mrs Deborah Efua Ennin _ Trip to Amsterdam_ 074 2425928687.pdf`\n- `Letter to NOK Investigation to Inquest Discussed ENNING G J 11052022 - Deborah ENNIN.docx` - related to father's death\n\nE) **Father's death documents** (GJ Enning / Godfried Joe Enning):\n- `Certificate of Fact of Death ENNING G J 11052022.pdf`\n- `BIOGRAPHY OF GODFRIED KOJO ENNING.docx`\n- `Elder Godfried Enning (Order of Service).docx`\n- `UCD35 GODFRIED JOE ENNING.pdf`\n- `GJ Enning Health In a nutshell.docx`\n- `GJEnninApril(2019)statements (1/2/3).pdf`\n- `GJEnning - GatewayGovUserID.pdf`\n- ~880+ Joe-Enning-Funeral-N.jpg images (funeral photos)\n\nF) **Work you (Andie) have done for her:**\n\n1. **Active PIP Review (PIP.1043 form, deadline was 12 March 2026)**\n   - The `Completing PIP Review Submission.md` and `PIP&Laura.md` are the AI sessions we did to break down all 12 PIP activities\n   - Activities 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 11, 12 - all worked on\n   - The most recent DWP letter is 23/04/2026 (MR Report) - this suggests the MR (Mandatory Reconsideration) was reviewed and there's an updated decision\n   - He has a filled form: `pip_ar1_filled.pdf`\n\n2. **Deborah_Plain_Language_Record.docx** - The big deliverable! A plain-language NHS medical record guide for mum, with the explicit purpose of \"Supporting evidence for PIP assessment\". Starts with Oct-Dec 2025. This is an EXCELLENT piece of work that's clearly being built iteratively.\n\n3. **Deborah_s_Health_Crossroads.pdf** (15 pages, Dec 2025) - The visual health intervention. Sent to mum saying \"for you to watch and understand maa\" with dietary advice. Either the precursor to the Plain Language Record, or a sister document with more visuals.\n\n4. **The WhatsApp coordination with Mum (_chat 12 (2).txt)** - 3 years of active care coordination: 2023-2026. Includes calls to Legal & General, INPS Italy, Laura Mills (welfare rights), Monzo bank, eye hospital, etc.\n\n5. **Ongoing care activities (May 2026)**:\n   - Booked her taxi (19/02/2026)\n   - Sent her Ghana passport scan (01/05/2026)\n   - Helped interpret medical letter from Acorn Medical Practice about Empagliflozin side effects (21/05/2026)\n   - Recent calls (03/06/2026)\n\n**Where we're at:**\n\nThe Plain Language Record is mid-build (only goes through October 2025). It was last saved when? Let me check. Actually I should check.\n\nThe DWP letter 23/04/2026 (MR Report) is a Mandatory Reconsideration letter - this is the next stage after the original PIP claim was disallowed. The MR letter from DWP is dated 23 April 2026. This is recent and very important.\n\nLooking at the chat:\n- 12/03/2026: Deadline for PIP review submission (and a missed call from mum)\n- 23/04/2026: \"Please just call em when you done reading\" - likely a follow-up to the MR letter being sent\n\nThe MR report on 23/04/2026 might be:\na) A confirmation the PIP review was received\nb) The MR decision (often unfavorable)\nc) Request for more information\nd) A new letter/decision\n\n**What to look at next:**\n\nBased on the most recent activity:\n1. **Read the MR Report - AE - 23.04.2026.pdf** to see what the DWP said after reviewing the PIP submission\n2. **Read the most recent DWP letter** to know the current state of her PIP claim\n3. **Continue building the Plain Language Record** - currently only covers Oct-Dec 2025, need to add 2026 entries including:\n   - The Mounjaro switch (5mg weekly injection since Feb 2026)\n   - The chronic disease reviews\n   - The cardiology/ophthalmology updates\n4. **Check the Empagliflozin leaflet from Acorn Medical Practice** that mum received 21/05/2026 - she needs to know about the side effects, especially given she's now on Mounjaro too\n5. **Follow up on the immigration stuff** - the chat shows Kevin's situation, Ghana travel, etc.\n6. **GP appointment follow-up** - the records show she needs insulin injections per the nurse recommendation (17/11/2025) - has this happened? Currently she's on Mounjaro which is a GLP-1 agonist, not insulin, but the records show she might still need insulin.\n\nLet me write this up as a comprehensive answer. The user said \"carry on\" so they want me to continue. I'll write a thorough summary that covers everything they asked for.\n\nAlso, I should note that the timing of today (2026-06-22) and the most recent chat (03/06/2026) suggests we're 3 weeks into the post-MR decision period. The user might need to take action on the MR decision (likely they have 1 month to appeal to tribunal - which would be 23 May 2026 = already passed? Or might still be active).\n\nLet me make sure I have my facts right. The MR Report dated 23/04/2026 means:\n- Original PIP review submitted around 12/03/2026\n- DWP MR decision sent 23/04/2026\n- 1 month to appeal to tribunal = 23/05/2026 (which has