the Health Crossroads content (or vice versa) - they appear to be related.\n\nActually re-reading: the docx read attempt succeeded because the Python script worked (it ignored the Add-Type error which was in PowerShell; Python ran separately via the `if` block). The content shown starts with \"NHS Patient Medical Record / Plain Language Guide for Mrs Deborah Ennin\" with a \"December 2025\" section. So the Plain Language Record IS dated December 2025.\n\nBut where does the Health_Crossroads.pdf fit? The chat on 06/12/2025 says \"Deborah_s_Health_Crossroads.pdf • 15 pages\" - and 15 pages matches the docx file's content depth. So Health_Crossroads.pdf is the PDF version of the Plain Language Record (or a closely related document).\n\nThe Read of Health_Crossroads.pdf returned \"File not found\" - maybe the file name has unusual characters or the path got truncated. Let me note this as a blocker.\n\nNow let me write the summary. I need to:\n- Be terse\n- Use bullets\n- Preserve exact paths\n- Keep all sections even if empty\n- Not mention the compaction\n\nLet me write it.",
